      • isPerspectivalized

        public boolean isPerspectivalized()
        Returns true if the perspectivalized attribute of this SemanticPredicate instance is set to true, false otherwise.

        This attribute is used when converting FrameNet to Uby-LMF. FrameNet frames which have a great diversity of lexical units, all of which share a kind of scene as a background are called non-perspectivalized frames. Such frames do not have a consistent set of semantic arguments (FEs in FrameNet terminology) for the target predicates, a consistent time assigned to the events or participants, or (most especially) a consistent point-of-view between target predicates.

        An example of a non-perspectivalized frame is the Performers and roles frame, which contains such diverse verbs as co-star, feature.

        Returns:
        true if the perspectivalized attribute of the semantic predicate is set, false otherwise
